      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@Jaskeyn once when the class is initiallized, yes. A class could be loaded/initiallized multiple times in some specific situations, which would run the static block multiple times.  But for the JVM those then constitute different classes (even if they have the same name)."
