    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>It's a block of code which is executed when the class gets loaded by a classloader. It is meant to do initialization of static members of the class.</p>\n\n<p>It is also possible to write non-static initializers, which look even stranger:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Foo {\n    {\n        // This code will be executed before every constructor\n        // but after the call to super()\n    }\n\n    Foo() {\n\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
