      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@aioobe I understand that it might not be necessary, but one will never learn of static initializers without being exposed to them. Also, in some cases class member initialization in the declaration is disencouraged (some companies I worked for), and initializing them inside static block or in the constructor (for non-static members) was the recommended practice."
