      "comment_id" : 27195205,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "I see. Why is it discouraged? Personally I find member initialization at the declaration quite easy to read and maintain. I would argue that forcing them into the constructors may a bad idea, especially if you have more than one constructor and need to repeat the initialization. (If you for instance change from ArrayList to LinkedList you need to remember to change it in multiple places.)"
    }, {
