      "creation_date" : 1441869155,
      "post_id" : 2943580,
      "comment_id" : 52850471,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "First of all, <code>labels.put(...)</code> is a statement, and you can&#39;t put statements directly in the class body. You <i>can</i> put them in the constructor, but then they would run each time a new <code>MyClass</code> object is created. By putting them in <code>static { ... }</code> you make sure these <code>put</code>-statements are executed once, when the class is loaded. (If this didn&#39;t answer your question, could you please post a snippet that explains what you suggest.)"
